<cite><a href="https://www.wisdomlib.org/" target="_blank" title="goto glossary/dictionary page">Source</a>: Wisdom Library: Dharma-samgraha</cite><p>Chandas (छन्दस्, “desire”) refers to one of the fourty <a href="/definition/samskara#buddhism">“conditions” (<em>saṃskāra</em>)</a> that are <a href="/definition/cittasamprayukta#buddhism">“associated with mind” (<em>citta-samprayukta</em>)</a> as defined in the Dharma-saṃgraha (section 30). The Dharma-samgraha (Dharmasangraha) is an extensive glossary of Buddhist technical terms in Sanskrit (e.g., <em>chandas</em>). The work is attributed to <a href="/definition/nagarjuna#buddhism">Nagarjuna</a> who lived around the 2nd century A.D.</p>
